00:13:58.650 --> 00:14:00.850
on Broadway for about 2 weeks.

00:14:00.850 --> 00:14:03.130 position:56%
And one of the night, every night
she would have a special guest come.

00:14:03.130 --> 00:14:05.050
And she had asked if I would
come and be a special guest

00:14:05.050 --> 00:14:07.550
that she was doing 50 Years
Long actually in her set.

00:14:07.550 --> 00:14:09.330
And she said, would you
come and be a special

00:14:09.330 --> 00:14:11.150
and maybe sing something
new because the audience,

00:14:11.150 --> 00:14:13.110
that would be kinky
for the audience.

00:14:13.110 --> 00:14:16.590
And so on Election Day
itself it was sort of like,

00:14:16.590 --> 00:14:19.570
hey I wonder what I'm going to sing
for Kristin's show, I have no idea.

00:14:19.570 --> 00:14:22.510
And then you know, the end
of the world and then I.

00:14:22.510 --> 00:14:29.200
[ Applause ]

00:14:29.200 --> 00:14:32.740
If you're not one of us it's fine,
just know that's how we feel.

00:14:32.740 --> 00:14:34.540
All right.

00:14:34.540 --> 00:14:42.040
[ Applause ]

00:14:42.040 --> 00:14:46.440
So I got up that morning and
I really thought I'm not going

00:14:46.440 --> 00:14:50.290
to go sing with Kristin Chenoweth,
that's not how that's going to go.

00:14:50.290 --> 00:14:53.340
But I thought well I can't
leave Kristin in the lurch,

00:14:53.340 --> 00:14:55.220
what am I supposed to sing?

00:14:55.220 --> 00:14:59.260
And I was like if I sing you know,
if I sing like the Old Red Hills

00:14:59.260 --> 00:15:02.010
of Home or [inaudible] it's
just, it's deeply hostile.

00:15:02.010 --> 00:15:05.940
There's just no way to and I
didn't want to be hostile, I didn't

00:15:05.940 --> 00:15:08.660
and especially if Kristin's show
which is all you know, sparkly

00:15:08.660 --> 00:15:10.950
and twirly and you
know all that stuff.

00:15:10.950 --> 00:15:13.570
And so I thought what
am I supposed to say.

00:15:13.570 --> 00:15:18.350 position:56%
The first two lines of the song
while I was making breakfast in sort

00:15:18.350 --> 00:15:21.500
of daze, because I don't think
any of us slept, I sort of,

00:15:21.500 --> 00:15:24.670
I said I've come to
sing a song about hope.

00:15:24.670 --> 00:15:27.670
And I don't mean it but that's
what I'm here to sing about.

00:15:27.670 --> 00:15:31.640
And so as I said that I thought,
I guess maybe I'll write a song.

00:15:31.640 --> 00:15:33.860
Maybe, I don't know what
time is it, can I, cause I,

00:15:33.860 --> 00:15:35.560
I'm a very slow writer in general

00:15:35.560 --> 00:15:37.570
but I thought I don't
know maybe I can do it.

00:15:37.570 --> 00:15:41.720
And we had to go that morning
my daughter was interviewing,

00:15:41.720 --> 00:15:44.170
she's going into 7th grade
and she was interviewing

00:15:44.170 --> 00:15:47.730
for a very schwansy [assumed
spelling] private girls school

00:15:47.730 --> 00:15:49.520
on the Upper East Side.

00:15:49.520 --> 00:15:53.180 position:56%
And so my wife and daughter went off
to go to the interview and I said,

00:15:53.180 --> 00:15:54.830
I'll meet you in a minute I
just have to take a shower.

00:15:54.830 --> 00:15:58.830 position:56%
And while I was in the shower I was
sort of working on the song and sort

00:15:58.830 --> 00:16:01.180
of coming up with it, which
again this is not my process

00:16:01.180 --> 00:16:04.560
but words were coming, words
were coming, words were coming.

00:16:04.560 --> 00:16:09.580
And I got in the cab
to go to the school

00:16:09.580 --> 00:16:14.050
and I wrote fear never
wins that's what I hope.

00:16:14.050 --> 00:16:17.270
See I said hope the work begins
as I was sitting in the cab.

00:16:17.270 --> 00:16:21.110
And I was just holding the note
pad open like that and I walked

00:16:21.110 --> 00:16:24.020 position:56%
into a girls' school which was like,

00:16:24.020 --> 00:16:26.340
that morning it was
like going to a wake.

00:16:26.340 --> 00:16:30.390
It was unbearable what it was
like and it was totally silent.

00:16:30.390 --> 00:16:33.820
But at the same time it was
this place that was all about,

00:16:33.820 --> 00:16:36.810
even in light of what had just
happened lifting girls you

00:16:36.810 --> 00:16:39.310
without saying to them you
can be what you want to be.

00:16:39.310 --> 00:16:42.190
You can be the best
things that you have to be.

00:16:42.190 --> 00:16:43.490
We will support you.

00:16:43.490 --> 00:16:44.790
We will be behind you.

00:16:44.790 --> 00:16:46.090
We will understand.

00:16:46.090 --> 00:16:47.950
And I thought while I'm sitting
there with this notepad in my hand

00:16:47.950 --> 00:16:50.550
that sings this song, I thought yes
this is exactly what I want to say.

00:16:50.550 --> 00:16:54.520
I want to be in this place right
now with this, with this sentiment.

00:16:54.520 --> 00:16:57.510
And our daughter was in doing
her interview and my wife

00:16:57.510 --> 00:17:00.660
and I was just sitting out
there sort of in shock you know.

00:17:00.660 --> 00:17:03.190
And she said to me,
what's on the pad?

00:17:03.190 --> 00:17:08.880 position:56%
And I said, I think it's a song that
I'm singing tonight for Kristin.

00:17:08.880 --> 00:17:12.680
And she said, well do you
want to show it to me?

00:17:12.680 --> 00:17:16.020
And I was about to start, just
in the hallway sort of singing it

00:17:16.020 --> 00:17:18.680
and I couldn't actually,
I tried to open my mouth

00:17:18.680 --> 00:17:20.220
and I started crying
and I said I can't yet.

00:17:20.220 --> 00:17:21.520
I can't do it yet.

00:17:21.520 --> 00:17:24.020
I don't even know if I'll be
able to do it tonight by I can.

00:17:24.020 --> 00:17:27.010
And so then we got done
with the interview,

00:17:27.010 --> 00:17:28.600
we dropped our daughter off
at school and we got back

00:17:28.600 --> 00:17:31.100
into the house and Hillary was
about to give her concession speech

00:17:31.100 --> 00:17:37.880 position:56%
and we went into my room with the
piano and I said all right I'm going

00:17:37.880 --> 00:17:41.710 position:56%
to do this and this is the only time
I'm going to do it before tonight,

00:17:41.710 --> 00:17:43.080
because I'm going to
have a nervous breakdown

00:17:43.080 --> 00:17:44.380
if I keep singing this song.

00:17:44.380 --> 00:17:45.680
So this is it.

00:17:45.680 --> 00:17:49.410
And I played it sort of, I
mean I hadn't put my hands

00:17:49.410 --> 00:17:50.970
on the piano at all
while writing it.

00:17:50.970 --> 00:17:52.530
You had asked me about
this this morning.

00:17:52.530 --> 00:17:55.120
I'm not usually a guy who can sort
of conceive all of this structure

00:17:55.120 --> 00:17:57.620
without writing anything down
or playing it, but I just sort

00:17:57.620 --> 00:17:59.120
of knew what the chords were.

00:17:59.120 --> 00:18:03.360
So I played it, we just sort of
had our moment to send in catharsis

00:18:03.360 --> 00:18:05.980
and then we went down
and watched the speech.

00:18:05.980 --> 00:18:10.580
